Copyleft Story License v1.0

1. Purpose
This license is designed to ensure that all works published under Realoid Fabrications remain free to use, share, adapt, and build upon in any medium or format, while protecting the authorship of their creators and preventing derivative works from being locked away under restrictive copyright.

2. Definitions
Founders: Dylsexia Fauxley and Fauch, co-founders of Realoid Fabrications.
Work: Any creative work released under this license, including but not limited to text, music, video, artwork, game systems, game assets, and multimedia storytelling projects.
Contributor: Any person other than the Founders who contributes material to a Work.
Derivative Work: Any adaptation, modification, remix, transformation, or extension of a Work.

3. Permissions
Subject to the conditions below, you are free to:
Use the Work for any purpose, including commercial use.
Copy and distribute the Work, in whole or in part.
Modify, adapt, or remix the Work into Derivative Works.
Publish and share Derivative Works.
Use in any medium or format, whether digital or physical, now existing or later developed.

4. Conditions
These permissions are granted under the following conditions:
Copyleft Requirement: Any Derivative Work must be released under this same license, Copyleft Story License v1.0 or any later version.
Attribution: All distributions of the Work or Derivative Works must give appropriate credit to the original authors and to Realoid Fabrications. Attribution should include, where relevant:
The name of the Work.
The names of the authors (Dylsexia Fauxley, Fauch, or other Contributors as credited).
A notice that the Work is released under the Copyleft Story License v1.0.
Integrity of License: You may not apply legal terms or technological measures that restrict others from doing anything this license permits.
Trademark Protection: The names Realoid Fabrications, Ash & Light, and Outremonde are trademarks of the Founders. While you may create and distribute Derivative Works, you may not use these names or present your work as the official product of Realoid Fabrications unless given explicit permission.

5. Founders’ Rights
All Works created by either Founder (Dylsexia Fauxley or Fauch) are jointly available to both, without restriction.
Neither Founder requires the other’s permission to use, adapt, or republish any Work released under Realoid Fabrications, including contributions authored by only one Founder.
In the event that one Founder is incapacitated or deceased, the other retains full rights to all Works under this license.

6. Contributors’ Rights
Contributors retain authorship of their own contributions.
By submitting work to be published under Realoid Fabrications, Contributors agree that their contributions are licensed under the Copyleft Story License v1.0 (or later), but they do not transfer ownership of authorship to the Founders.
Contributors must be credited in all uses of their contributions.

7. Warranty Disclaimer
All Works are provided “as is,” without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.

8. Jurisdiction
This license applies globally, to the maximum extent permitted by applicable law.

